<paragraph blockId="7.[136,1452,1467,2092]" pageId="7" pageNumber="178">
Carpels divergent, lanceolate, slightly split ends, ca. 
<quantity box="[788,857,1467,1494]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="178" unit="mm" value="5.0">5 mm</quantity>
, base connate for ca. 
<quantity box="[1104,1173,1467,1494]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="178" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
, apex slightly divergent. Style ca. 
<quantity box="[242,308,1503,1529]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="178" unit="mm" value="2.0">2 mm</quantity>
long. Follicles divergent, many seeded. Seeds brown, ovoid, 0.3–0.8 × 
<quantity box="[1121,1261,1503,1529]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="178" unit="mm" value="0.3" valueMax="0.4" valueMin="0.2">0.2–0.4 mm</quantity>
. Flowering early April, fruiting April–May. (
<figureCitation box="[443,539,1538,1564]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[136,229,2032,2054]" captionTargetBox="[166,1422,709,1996]" captionTargetId="figure-205@6.[151,1435,695,2019]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Sedum spiralifolium sp. nov. A. Habit in flowering period; B. Sterile shoots (twisted upper leaves at the top of the sterile shoots); C. Inflorescence; D. Flowering plant; E. Nectar scale; F. Follicles; G. Seed." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5151487" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5151487/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="178">Figure 3</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation box="[593,610,1538,1564]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[136,229,1364,1386]" captionTargetBox="[297,1306,187,1328]" captionTargetId="figure-17@7.[262,1326,169,1344]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Sedum spiralifolium sp. nov. A. Flowering plant; B. Petal with stamen; C. Twisted leaves of the sterile shoot; D. Flower; E. Nectar scale; F. Carpels; G. Seed. (Drawn by Hai-Yan Cao from the holotype in ACM)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5151489" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5151489/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="178">4</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
